 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Visualizing Chipotle's Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Click the button below to run this notebook directly on Google Colab:\n",
    "\n",
    "[<img src=\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\" align=\"left\">](https://colab.research.google.com/github)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "This time we are going to pull data directly from the internet.\n",
    "Special thanks to: https://github.com/justmarkham for sharing the dataset and materials.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Step 1. Import the necessary libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 2. Import the dataset from this [address](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/chipotle.tsv)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 3. Assign it to a variable called chipo."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/chipotle.tsv'\n",
    "chipo = pd.read_csv(url, sep='\\t')\n",
    "chipo.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 4. See the first 10 entries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "chipo.head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 5. Create a histogram of the top 5 items bought"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "top_5 = chipo.groupby('item_name').quantity.sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(5)\n",
    "\n",
    "top_5.plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Items')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Times Ordered')\n",
    "plt.title('Most ordered Chipotle\\'s Items')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 6. Create a scatterplot with the number of items ordered per order price\n",
    "#### Hint: Price should be in the X-axis and Items ordered in the Y-axis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if chipo['item_price'].dtype == 'object':\n",
    "    chipo['item_price'] = chipo['item_price'].str.replace('$', '').astype(float)\n",
    "\n",
    "orders = chipo.groupby('order_id').sum(numeric_only=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(x=orders.item_price, y=orders.quantity, s=50, c='blue', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Order Price ($)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Items Ordered')\n",
    "plt.title('Number of items ordered per order price')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 7. BONUS: Create a question and a graph to answer your own question."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Question: What is the distribution of prices for all individual items sold?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,\n    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }\n   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "chipo['single_item_price'] = chipo['item_price'] / chipo['quantity']\n",
    "unique_items = chipo.groupby('item_name').single_item_price.as_index().first() if hasattr(chipo.groupby('item_name').single_item_price, 'as_index') else chipo.groupby('item_name').single_item_price.first()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.hist(unique_items, bins=10, color='green', edgecolor='black')\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Single Item Prices')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Price ($)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Count of Unique Items')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
